<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Avdeev" authorityYear="1987" class="Hexanauplia" family="Lichomolgidae" genus="Herrmannella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Herrmannella dentata" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dentata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Herrmannella dentata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was originally described as an associate of the bivalves 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Jay" authorityYear="1857" class="Bivalvia" family="Myidae" genus="Mya" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Mya japonica" order="Myida" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="japonica">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Mya japonica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Jay, 1857 and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Yokoyama" baseAuthorityYear="1922" class="Bivalvia" family="Psammobiidae" genus="Gari" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Gari kazusensis" order="Cardiida" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="kazusensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Gari kazusensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Yokoyama, 1922) in the Peter the Great Bay, Russia (
<bibRefCitation author="Avdeev, GV" journalOrPublisher="Zoologicheskoy Zhurnal" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="608 - 613" refId="B1" refString="Avdeev, GV, 1987. Two new copepod species (Sabelliphilidae, Poecilostomatoida) from bivalvian molluscs in the Peter the Great Bay of the Japan Sea. Zoologicheskoy Zhurnal 66 (4): 608 - 613" title="Two new copepod species (Sabelliphilidae, Poecilostomatoida) from bivalvian molluscs in the Peter the Great Bay of the Japan Sea." volume="66" year="1987">Avdeev 1987</bibRefCitation>
). In Korea, this copepod species has been found only from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" class="Bivalvia" family="Myidae" genus="Mya" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Mya arenaria" order="Myida" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="arenaria">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Mya arenaria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Linnaeus, 1758 (previously reported as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Makiyama" authorityYear="1935" class="Bivalvia" family="Myidae" genus="Mya" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Mya arenaria subsp. oonogai" order="Myida" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Mollusca" rank="subSpecies" species="arenaria" subSpecies="oonogai">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Mya arenaria oonogai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Makiyama, 1935) on the south coast.
</paragraph>
